Package: HeckmanSelect
Title: Penalized Estimation for Bivariate Probit Model with Sample Selection
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Emmanuel", "Ogundimu",
           email = "emmanuel.ogundimu@durham.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements lasso and adaptive-lasso (via HeckSelect) and 
    ridge (via RidgeBPSS) penalized estimation for the 
    bivariate probit sample-selection model. Supports Normal-error 
    and Ali-Mikhail-Haq (AMH) copula dependence structures. Includes 
    bootstrap optimism-corrected internal validation with 
    metric-specific paired optimism (AUC, AUPR, Brier, ECE, MCE). 
    Designed for reject inference in credit scoring and related 
    selection-bias applications. The package includes the American 
    Express credit card dataset (Greene 1998) as an example.
